            <entry xml:id="entry_calx" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>calx</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3277e69"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>колесо</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>wheel</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3277e81">
                        <quote>calxy ḱʼīl</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">обод колеса</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">wheel rim</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3277e98">
                        <quote>calxy dændag</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">спица</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">radius</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> („зуб колеса“)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (wheel tooth)</note>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3277e121">
                        <quote>calxy mæskʼ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">ступица</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">hob</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3277e138">
                        <quote>k˳yrojy calx</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">мельничная турбина</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">mill's wheel</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3277e155">
                        <quote>Ojnoni calx Soslani marunmæ ærcudæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>колесо Ойнона пришло убить Сослана</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Ojnon's wheel came to kill Soslan</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            19</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3277e175">
                        <quote>mæj jæ calxy ʒag ū</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>луна находится в фазе полнолуния („в полное колесо“)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the moon is in the full moon phase ("full wheel")</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Общее индоевропейское слово. Исходная древнеиранская форма —
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e193" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*čaxra-</w></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e198" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e203" xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>čark</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e208" xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>carx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e213" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*čaxr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e219" xml:lang="sog"><w>*čarx-(čɣrh,
                            črɣ-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e222" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>čaxra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e227" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čakra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e232" xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>κύκλος</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e237" xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>hweohl</w></mentioned>, без удвоения начального согласного — <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e242" xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">коло</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e249" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>колесо</w></mentioned>. Широко распространилось (под влиянием
                    персидского, а возможно и скифо-аланского) в кавказских языках: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e254" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>čʼaxr</w>
                        <gloss><q>вращение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e262" xml:lang="xcl"><w>čaxarak</w>
                        <gloss><q>прялка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e268" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>čarxi</w>
                        <gloss><q>станок</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e276" xml:lang="lzz"><lang/>
                        <w>čʼarxa</w>
                        <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e284" xml:lang="lzz"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>часть ткацкого станка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e291" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w>
                        <gloss><q>точило</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e299" xml:lang="ani"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w>
                        <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e307" xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w>
                        <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e315" xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>šarx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e320" xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w>
                        <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. Сюда же <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e328" xml:lang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>čark</w>
                        <gloss><q>колесо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e337" xml:lang="tr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сфера</q></gloss></mentioned>. Для объяснения %iI%i в %icalx%i
                    приходится исходить из производной формы *%ičaxrya%i- (%iг%i перед %iy%i →
                    %il%i). Ср. другие слова из круга ‘колесо—колесница’: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wærdon"/> ‘арба’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rætænaǧd"/>
                    ‘оглобля’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ar"/> ‘оглобля’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50, 78, III
                            159</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>26</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>I
                        54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">A common Indo-European word. The initial Old Iranian form is
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e365" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*čaxra-</w></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e370" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e375" xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>čark</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e380" xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>carx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e385" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*čaxr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e391" xml:lang="sog"><w>*čarx-(čɣrh,
                            črɣ-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e394" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>čaxra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e399" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čakra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e404" xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>κύκλος</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e409" xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>hweohl</w></mentioned>, without doubling of the initial consonant —
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e414" xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>kolo</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e420" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>koleso</w></mentioned>. The word is widespread in Caucasian languages
                    (under the influence of Persian and probably Scythian-Alan): <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e425" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>čʼaxr</w>
                        <gloss><q>rotation</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e433" xml:lang="xcl"><w>čaxarakʼ</w>
                        <gloss><q>spinning-wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e439" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>čarxi</w>
                        <gloss><q>lathe</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e447" xml:lang="lzz"><lang/>
                        <w>čʼarxa</w>
                        <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e455" xml:lang="lzz"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>part of a weaver loom</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e462" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w>
                        <gloss><q>grindstone</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e470" xml:lang="ani"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w>
                        <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e478" xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w>
                        <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e486" xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>šarx</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e491" xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/>
                        <w>čarx</w>
                        <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. Also here <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e499" xml:lang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>čark</w>
                        <gloss><q>wheel</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3277e508" xml:lang="tr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>sphere</q></gloss></mentioned>. To explain %iI%i in %icalx%i we
                    have to assume a derivated from *%ičaxrya%i- (%iг%i before %iy%i → %il%i). Cf.
                    other words in the field ‘wheel—chariot’: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wærdon"/> ‘bullock-cart’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rætænaǧd"/> ‘shaft’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ar"/> ‘shaft’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50, 78, III
                        159</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>26</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>I 54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
